# Unity MCP — sequential calls only

The Unity MCP server (`user-unity-mcp`) does **not** support parallel tool calls.

When using Unity MCP:

- Issue **exactly one** `CallMcpTool` to `user-unity-mcp` per assistant turn.
- Wait for that call to finish before issuing the next Unity MCP call.
- Do **not** batch multiple Unity MCP tools in the same message, even when they are independent.
- Other tools (grep, read, shell, non-Unity MCP servers) may still run in parallel with a single Unity MCP call.

If a task needs several Unity operations, run them one at a time across multiple turns.
